The paper discusses vulnerabilities and threats related to optical TEMPEST, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of standardised PHY solutions in Ethernet, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT). The discussion of new trends such as the Internet of Things (IoT) and High Frequency Trading (HFT) suggests that the paper may also be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
